article.description: — Dre Davis' 28 points helped Seton Hall defeat DePaul 86-62 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Davis scores 28, Seton Hall defeats DePaul 86-62
article.linkText: Davis scores 28, Seton Hall defeats DePaul 86-62
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- — Dre Davis' 28 points helped Seton Hall defeat DePaul 86-62 on Saturday night. Davis added seven rebounds for the Pirates (20-11, 13-7 Big East Conference). Dylan Addae-Wusu scored 19 points, going 6 of 12 from the floor, including 3 for 8 from 3-point range, and 4 for 6 from the foul line. Kadary Richmond shot 3 of 9 from the field and 4 for 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 11 points, while adding three steals. Chico Carter Jr. led the Blue Demons (3-28, 0-20) in scoring, finishing with 16 points. DePaul also got 12 points and two blocks from Jeremiah Oden. Elijah Fisher had 10 points and two blocks. The loss is the 19th in a row for the Blue Demons. Seton Hall took the lead with 13:02 remaining in the first half and did not give it up. The score was 35-26 at halftime, with Davis racking up 12 points. Davis scored 16 points in the second half to help lead the way as Seton Hall went on to secure a victory, outscoring DePaul by 15 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
